<emphasis id="BFBB56F96B216EB0E704DD51360758AB" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Paratypes</emphasis>
: 1 ♂, 1 ♀, same data as for holotype (JSO).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="93ABC30D839B08460921428D9351CCF3" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="AC5799400AC4324398324433AFECC071" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C5A6F27BDF5EE991386D69744E7EE53F" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">
The new species is named in honour of the late Prof. Dr. 
<normalizedToken id="12C73833876B155EFD8126E306786DE6" originalValue="Tomáš">Tomas</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="00856BF52B64FA17BEA3F11B426D621A" originalValue="Soldán">Soldan</normalizedToken>
, an outstanding 
<taxonomicName id="B831BA205F687ED1C5B88723C6D6ED81" lsidName="" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" rank="order">Ephemeroptera</taxonomicName>
specialist. A noun in genitive singular.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="69A69D5573A4314B0AE26617C9BC7E2F" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="DA8B71D19D09DB7C3C2335562B13D8A7" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B5C5EDB9521C4BDA3C7102C4631C461C" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">The new species is distinctive by the combination of the quadrangular outline of its dorsal portion of gonocoxite and an unusually shaped inner gonostylus with three distinct teeth on the dorsal surface. The type specimens were dried from ethanol; hence, their body colouration might be darker in a normal dried state.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
